&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Research Nurse / Practitioner&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a band 5 Research Nurse to work with our experienced Research Team; dedicated to the treatment and care offered to patients taking part in clinical trials.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The varied Trials portfolio covers both randomised controlled trials, and observational studies in many different specialties.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will need be organised, motivated and able to prioritise their own workload. They will be responsible for data collection and, working under supervision, will be required to support the team with recruitment into trials. A key part of the role will be to liaise with all members of the multi-disciplinary team so the successful candidate must possess excellent interpersonal and communication skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an excellent opportunity for those who wish to start a career in clinical research. Training will be provided for research specific procedures.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information, please contact: Briony Dillon, Research Team Leader, Torbay Hospital, Telephone: 01803 656611&lt;/p&gt;
